					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records the tax-free gift of a quarter <hi rend="italic">(vēli)</hi> of dry land below the tank by the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> (assembly) of Neṟkuppai, for offerings to Sūryadēva (in the temple) at Tirumudukuṉṟam. This was later converted into wet land by the efforts of one <hi rend="bold">Kāvidikkuḍi Kulamānaṉ Kūttaṉ</hi> mentioned in No. 303 above. Both these inscriptions seem to be assignable to <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
